- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with mathematical structures such as groups and relations. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper touches on the topic of computable subgroups of $(\QQ,+)$ which could have applications in cryptography. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on algorithms or data structures, but rather on the theoretical foundations of computability and logic.
